==English==
===Etymology===
From [[sodium bicarbonate]], originally a [[constituent]] of soda water.
===Noun===
'''soda water'''
# Water saturated with [[carbon dioxide]] and stored under pressure in a bottle. Usually mixed before drinking.
#: ''[[Scotch]] and [[soda]]'' &ndash; a mixture of [[Scotch whisky]] and soda water.

